*Modification*
==============
1. Merging the training and the test sets to create one data set.
2. Extracting only the measurements on the mean and standard deviation for each measurement.
3. Useing descriptive activity names to name the activities in the data set
4. Appropriately labeling the data set with descriptive variable names.
5. Independent tidy data set with the average of each variable for each activity and each subject.

*Identifiers*
=============
Subject: the ID of the Subject
Activity: the name of the activity performed by the subject when measurements were taken

*Variables*
===========
1. x_train, y_train, x_test, y_test, s_train and s_test contain the data from UCI HAR Dataset.
2. x_data, y_data and s_data merge the previous datasets.
3. Feature contains the names for the x_data, applied to the column names from features.txt.
4. act_label contains the activity names from activity_labels.txt
5. all_data is combination of x_data, y_data and s_data.
6. meltd_data is literally melted data by melt() function from reshape2 package.

